AB  - 
                   NOVELTY - Nutritionally regulating and increasing carbon sequestration in wetland carbon sinks, comprises: (i) determining the wetland type by selecting a meadow or marsh ground without stagnant water; (ii) determining the soil moisture content by testing ground vegetation soil, filling fresh soil samples in soil box, and drying, determining the wetland type soil, performing white slurry soil formation process on the upper soil layer by dividing into four layers, and performing marsh soil formation by dividing the soil surface organic matter into two layers; and (iii) applying nutrients.
                    USE - The method is useful for nutritionally regulating and increasing carbon sequestration in wetland carbon sinks.
                    ADVANTAGE - The method improves wetland vegetation coverage and carbon sequestration capability, increases soil carbon storage, reduces greenhouse gas emissions, reduces investment cost, and is economical.
                    DETAILED DESCRIPTION - Nutritionally regulating and increasing carbon sequestration in wetland carbon sinks, comprises: (i) determining the wetland type by selecting a meadow or marsh ground without stagnant water, where the meadow is grown with perennial herbaceous plant in the community type, which is formed and developed under moderate moisture conditions, and the marsh is a kind of planting type which is formed under more water and over-wet conditions; (ii) determining the wetland environmental factors by (a) determining the moisture content of the soil by taking at 5-15 cm under ground vegetation soil for testing, using a soil box to fill the fresh soil sample under the vegetation, and drying to constant weight at 80 degrees C, where the (soil moisture content is equal to (soil wet weight - soil dry weight) divide by soil dry weight x 100%) and the soil moisture content is 60-95%, and (b) determining the wetland type soil, removing the soil, weed and dried object on the surface layer (3-5 cm), vertically digging a pit with a length of 80 cm, a width of 50 cm and a depth of 120-200 cm, measuring the depth with metric rule and digging from the bottom to top, taking the meadow soil, which is provided with obvious humus accumulation process and retention sterile process, dividing the process into a humus layer, a retention sterile layer and a gley layer, where the humus layer has high humus content with a thickness of 20-50 cm, dark gray-gray colored with the structure in the form of pellet or granular, the retention layer has low humus content, and multiple iron manganese concretion, gradually reduced, and the gley layer has gray-green, green or white and grayish yellow with rust plaques formation, scattered soil structure with silt loam soil and partial stickiness; (c) performing white slurry soil formation process only on the upper soil layer by dividing into four layers using the meadow surface layer-retention sterility-leaching process, humus layer with a thickness of 10-20 cm, having high humus content, when the humus layer is wet, it is dark gray in color, the white slurry layer has a thickness of 20 cm with off-white or pale yellow in color when it is wet, removing white slurry by rain to form silt sand, the white silica powder is firm with less plant roots and very low content of organic matter, and a sticky deposition layer with a thickness is 120-160 cm and color of brown to dark brown, small prismatic structure or prism shaped structure called as garlic soil, which is a parent material usually less than 200 cm, heavy quality with brown or yellow-brown color; and (d) performing soil formation in marsh soil comprises dividing the peat and gleization soil layer of the organic matter on the soil surface layer into a peat layer and a gley layer, where the peat layer is located in the upper part of the marsh soil and the thickness is based on the presence of an embedding layer, having a thickness of 10-50 cm, is obtained by partial decomposition or decomposition of organic residues, when the peat layer is not decomposed it is yellow-brown in color and the color under partial decomposition is brown or black, and the gley layer is located on the lower part of the marsh soil, and ensuring the soil type to be meadow soil, white slurry soil or marsh soil; and (iii) selecting nutrient substance e.g. nitrogenous fertilizer, phosphate fertilizer and potash fertilizer, and applying during 15th to 30th May in the sunny afternoon weather, where the amount of fertilizer applied (in kg/acre) comprises nitrogenous fertilizer (3.5-4.5), phosphate fertilizer (2.5-3.5) and potash fertilizer (2-2.5).
