AB  - This chapter gives an overview of redox processes occurring within surface waters, sediments, and sediment pore waters of estuaries. Attention is given to parameters inducing stratification and redox zonation, as well as related differences between river deltas and fjords. Factors affecting metal speciation, mobility, and availability in oxic estuarine environments are discussed, followed by the role of redox processes when the estuarine environment evolves toward anoxic conditions. Thereafter, focus is on the fate of metals as affected by occasional oxidation of reduced environments. Physicochemical extraction methods that are helpful to assess risks related to the presence of metals in estuarine floodplain soils and sediments are discussed.
